contentrichtext.text: {{Taxobox | name = ''Quiscalus'' | image = GrackleInFlight.jpg | image_width = | image_caption = [[Common Grackle]], ''Quiscalus quiscula'' | regnum = [[Animal]]ia | phylum = [[Chordate|Chordata]] | classis = [[bird|Aves]] | ordo = [[Passerine|Passeriformes]] | familia = [[Icterid]]ae | genus = '''''Quiscalus''''' | genus_authority = [[Louis Jean Pierre Vieillot|Vieillot]], 1816 | subdivision_ranks = [[Species]] | subdivision = * ''Quiscalus major'' * ''Quiscalus quiscula'' * ''Quiscalus mexicanus'' * ''Quiscalus palustris'' <small>([[extinct]])</small> * ''Quiscalus nicaraguensis'' * ''Quiscalus niger'' * ''Quiscalus lugubris'' }} The [[bird|avian]] genus '''''Quiscalus''''' contains six of the ten species of [[grackle]], gregarious [[passerine]] [[bird]]s in the [[Icterid]] family. They are native to [[North America|North]] and [[South America]]. The six species are: * [[Boat-tailed Grackle]], ''Quiscalus major'' * [[Common Grackle]], ''Quiscalus quiscula'' * [[Great-tailed Grackle]], ''Quiscalus mexicanus'' * [[Slender-billed Grackle]], ''Quiscalus palustris'' - [[extinct]] (1910) * [[Nicaraguan Grackle]], ''Quiscalus nicaraguensis'' * [[Greater Antillean Grackle]], ''Quiscalus niger'' * [[Carib Grackle]], ''Quiscalus lugubris'' ==External links== *[http://ibc.lynxeds.com/family/troupials-allies-icteridae Quiscalus videos, photos and sounds] on the Internet Bird Collection [[Category:Quiscalus|*]] [[Category:Bird genera]] {{Icteridae-stub}}
